member.summary: Uploads contents of the file to the image store. Used by IApplicationClient.UploadApplicationPackageAsync to trace a request Id associated with original Uplaod call.

member.name: M:Microsoft.ServiceFabric.Client.Http.ImageStoreClient.UploadFileChunkAsync(System.Byte[],System.String,System.Nullable{System.Guid},System.Int64,System.Int64,System.Int64,System.String,System.Nullable{System.Int64},System.Threading.CancellationToken)
member.summary: Uploads a file chunk to the image store relative path. Used by IApplicationClient.UploadApplicationPackageAsync to trace a request Id associated with original Uplaod call.
member.param: Byte array containing file chunk to upload.
Relative path to file or folder in the image store from its root.
A GUID generated by the user for a file uploading. It identifies an image store upload session which keeps track of all file chunks until it is committed.
The start position of the chunk in byte array represnting file contents.
The end position of the chunk in byte array representing file contents.
The size, in bytes, of the file for which chunk is to be uploaded.
Request Id to use for tracing.

The server timeout for performing the operation in seconds. This specifies the time duration that the client is willing to wait for the requested operation to complete. The default value for this parameter is 60 seconds.
member.returns: A task that represents the asynchronous operation.
member.remarks: When uploading file chunks to the image store, the Content Range information is sent to server. Example: if the total file length is 20,000 bytes, and chunk being uploaded is for first 5,000 bytes, value of would be 0, value of would be 4999 and value of would be 20000.
